---

## Reverse Diffusion Process

The neural network learns to remove noise step by step.

Instead of predicting the image directly, the model predicts the added noise.

Loss Function:

Mean Squared Error (MSE)

between

Actual Noise

and

Predicted Noise

---

## Diffusion Model Architecture

Studied the role of **U-Net** as the backbone of diffusion models.

Components:

- Encoder (Downsampling)
- Bottleneck
- Decoder (Upsampling)
- Skip Connections
- Time Embeddings

---

## Stable Diffusion

Learned the architecture of Stable Diffusion.

Main Components:

### Variational Autoencoder (VAE)

- Compresses images into latent space
- Decodes latent vectors back to images

### U-Net

- Performs denoising in latent space

### Text Encoder

- Converts text prompts into embeddings
- Enables text-to-image generation

